The paper deals with the problem of timely exchange of updates between a central station and a set of ground terminals via a mobile agent that traverses across the ground terminals along a mobility graph. This problem involves information theory, networking, and graph theory, which are all covered by the arXiv categories cs.IT, cs.NI, and cs.SI. The paper also proposes randomized trajectories and analyzes their performance, which falls under the category of randomized algorithms and probabilistic analysis, covered by cs.DS and cs.LG. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.IT, cs.NI, and cs.SI, followed by cs.DS and cs.LG.
